tables.City: 2010 Host City Election — ballot bidding results

In Canada, three cities expressed interest in bidding for the Games. Along with Vancouver, the eventual winner of the bid for the 2010 Games, the Canadian Olympic Association considered bids from Calgary, Alberta (host of the 1988 Winter Olympics ) and Quebec City , Quebec (a candidate for the 2002 Winter Olympics ).  Vancouver was chosen to represent Canada. Previously, Calgary had beat Vancouver for the Canadian bid in 1988. Vancouver's bid evaluation was very positive, with only minor issues. The Bid Committee's plan to make the games environmentally sustainable and to incorporate the First Nations people was greatly applauded. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The budget plan was deemed quite achievable. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The venues constructed specifically for the games needed minor improvements. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The plan for the Paralympics was stated to be "very compact". IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 There was concern about traffic noise at the Vancouver Olympic Village, but the Bid Committee satisfied the Commission with assurances that the buildings would have major sound insulation. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 Security and accommodation plans were considered to be excellent. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 Minor improvement was needed in the transportation area. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003

In evaluating Pyeongchang's bid, the Commission found several issues. They were concerned that environmental issues at the alpine skiing, downhill skiing, and ski jumping venues had not properly been met. However, they did comment that local opinion in this area was positive. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 During their evaluation, the commission also discovered that the OCOG had increased their budget by US$150 million. A further US$3.4 billion was budgeted by other organizations, primarily for road and rail improvements. These improvements were deemed inadequate by the Commission. The budget was also seen as being underestimated. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The slalom course, the Peace Valley venues, and the downhill and Super G venue was deemed inadequate at the time of evaluation. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The budget for many venues was found to be either inadequate or overly high. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The Commission noted that Korea had little experience in organizing winter sporting events for the disabled, and much work would need to be done in order to host the Paralympics. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The three proposed Olympic villages were deemed acceptable. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The security plans were also deemed acceptable. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The Commission stated that the current accommodations in Pyeongchang were woefully inadequate. There was low capacity and multiple differing standards. They also found that accommodations for many sponsors were up to fifty kilometers from the venues. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The transportation plan was deemed to be capable of supporting the Games. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 Korean broadcasters were found to need international training and experience. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 Pyeongchang was later chosen as the host city of the 2018 Winter Olympics and the 2024 Winter Youth Olympics .

The evaluation of Salzburg's bid was generally positive, however there were some issues. Concern was noted that the OCOG might not able to meet their proposed budget of US$901.4 million. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 Cost formulas were also needed for sponsor accommodations. Transportation between venues was deemed excellent. However, the snowboarding venue would have to be changed, and there were logistical issues at the Nordic combined and ski jumping venue. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The Bid Committee was found to not have adequately planned for the Paralympics. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The three proposed Olympic Villages were deemed excellent. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 Security plans were stated to be well-thought out. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 There was concern that accommodations might be too expensive for guests. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003 The transportation plan was found to be in need of further development. IOC Evaluation Commission 2003
